Directors: Larry Bishop
Studio: Weinstein Company
Run Time: 80 minutes
Synopsis:
Veteran AIP genre star Larry Bishop (son of famed Rat Packer Joey Bishop)
directs and stars in this gritty revenge tale concerning a biker gang 
that rallies to avenge the violent murder of a fellow gang member. 
An homage to such classic biker films as Chrome and Hot Leather and 
Angel Unchained, Hell Ride was conceived when director Bishop was invited
to Quentin Tarantino&#039;s home to view a print of The Savage Seven. 
Upon realizing that there hadn&#039;t been a true biker film in years, the 
pair quickly contacted Bob Weinstein and conspired to produce a lean and
mean two-wheeled revenge flick that would more 
than make up for lost time.
